 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Added — packaged installs (Homebrew, AUR, bash one-liner)
+
+- **XDG global layout** by default: config `~/.config/hive/`, data `~/.local/share/hive/`, state `~/.local/state/hive/`, cache `~/.cache/hive/`. `HIVE_HOME` keeps the legacy single-directory layout for tests and power users. One-time copy-migration from `~/Dev/hive/config.yml` when XDG config is absent.
+- **Release tarballs** via `packaging/scripts/build_tarball.sh` and `.github/workflows/release.yml` (tag `v*` → linux-x86_64 + darwin-arm64 assets + `SHA256SUMS` + `install.sh`). Relocatable prefix with vendored gems; optional embedded Ruby from the build host.
+- **Install channels:** Homebrew formula staging (`packaging/homebrew/hive.rb` → tap `ivankuznetsov/hive`), AUR `hive-bin` (`packaging/aur/hive-bin/`), bash installer (`packaging/install.sh`) with `hv` fallback on Apache Hive name collision.
+- **CLI:** `hive update` (channel-native only; `--check` / `--dry-run`), `hive uninstall` (preserves state/work by default; `--purge` drops bash payload only).
+- **`hive init`** can register systemd-user / launchd daemon units with an explicit enable+start prompt; non-TTY skips service registration.
+- **`hive doctor`** reports runtime CLI soft-deps (`git`, `gh`, `jq`, `claude`, …) with install hints; missing soft-deps do not fail the skill exit code.
+- **Agent install prompt:** `packaging/INSTALL_PROMPT.md`. Skills remain marketplace-only (not part of the core binary).
+- Docs: `docs/install.md`; README / getting-started lead with packaged channels. Project pipeline path remains `<project>/.hive-state/`.
+
 ### Added — opt-in interactive tmux brainstorm runtime
 
 - `brainstorm.runtime: tmux_interactive` runs stage `2-brainstorm` in a fresh per-task tmux session (`hive-2-brainstorm-<slug>`) with interactive `claude`, while preserving the existing `brainstorm.md` WAITING/COMPLETE marker contract.
