@@ -0,0 +1,121 @@
+# Install Hive
+
+Hive ships as platform tarballs with a vendored gem tree (and, on release CI, an embedded Ruby runtime) so tier-1 users do not need a source checkout at `~/Dev/hive`.
+
+**Tier-1:** macOS arm64, Ubuntu 22.04+ x86_64, Arch Linux x86_64.
+
+## Recommended channels
+
+| Platform | Command |
+|----------|---------|
+| macOS | `brew tap ivankuznetsov/hive && brew install hive` |
+| Arch | `yay -S hive-bin` |
+| Other Linux | `curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh \| bash` |
+
+Agent-driven install: paste [packaging/INSTALL_PROMPT.md](../packaging/INSTALL_PROMPT.md) into Claude Code / Codex / Pi.
+
+### Homebrew (own tap)
+
+```bash
+brew tap ivankuznetsov/hive
+brew install hive
+hive --version
+```
+
+Formula staging lives in-repo at [packaging/homebrew/hive.rb](../packaging/homebrew/hive.rb) for the `ivankuznetsov/homebrew-hive` tap. This is **not** homebrew-core (v1). Tier-1 bottles: **darwin-arm64** and **linux-x86_64** only (no darwin-x86_64 until tier-2 CI builds it).
+
+On each `v*` tag the release workflow rewrites `url`/`sha256` via [packaging/scripts/bump_package_metadata.sh](../packaging/scripts/bump_package_metadata.sh) and attaches the formula to the GitHub Release. When the `HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN` secret is set, it also pushes `Formula/hive.rb` to `ivankuznetsov/homebrew-hive`.
+
+### AUR `hive-bin`
+
+```bash
+yay -S hive-bin
+# or: paru -S hive-bin
+hive --version
+```
+
+Package sources: [packaging/aur/hive-bin/](../packaging/aur/hive-bin/). The package name is always `hive-bin`; the binary installs as `/usr/bin/hive`.
+
+AUR is **not** auto-pushed (needs AUR credentials). Each release attaches a `PKGBUILD` with a single tarball source and a real `sha256sums` entry derived from `SHA256SUMS`. Maintainers copy those assets into the AUR package and push.
+
+### Bash one-liner
+
+```bash
+curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash
+# pin a release:
+HIVE_VERSION=v0.1.0 curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash
+```
+
+Installs under XDG paths by default:
+
+| Path | Role |
+|------|------|
+| `~/.local/bin/hive` (or `hv`) | launcher on PATH |
+| `~/.local/share/hive/` | package prefix + `install-channel` marker |
+| `~/.config/hive/config.yml` | global project registry |
+| `~/.local/state/hive/` | daemon/bot pid + logs |
+| `~/.cache/hive/` | cache |
+
+If another `hive` binary is already on PATH and does not look like this project (e.g. Apache Hive), the installer installs as **`hv`** instead.
+
+### After any channel
+
+```bash
+hive doctor          # skills + runtime CLI soft-checks (git, gh, jq, claude, …)
+cd your-project
+hive init .          # creates .hive-state/; may prompt for daemon user service
+hive tui
+```
+
+Runtime CLIs (`git`, `gh`, `claude`, `jq`, …) are **not** auto-installed. Doctor and the bash installer only report missing tools with hints.
+
+## Lifecycle
+
+```bash
+hive update          # shells out to brew / yay / install.sh — never in-place swap on brew/AUR
+hive update --check  # print current vs latest GitHub release tag
+hive uninstall       # remove service + bash hooks; preserves state and project work
+hive uninstall --purge  # also drop bash package payload under share (still keeps state/work)
+```
+
+## XDG and `HIVE_HOME`
+
+- Default global layout is XDG (see table above).
+- Set `HIVE_HOME` to force the legacy single-directory layout (`$HIVE_HOME/config.yml`, `$HIVE_HOME/logs/`) used by tests and power users.
+- On first read, if `~/.config/hive/config.yml` is missing but `~/Dev/hive/config.yml` exists, Hive **copies** the file into the XDG path and prints a one-line notice. The old tree is never deleted automatically.
+
+Project pipeline state remains at **`<project>/.hive-state/`** (not renamed in v1).
+
+## Skills package
+
+Claude Code / Codex / Pi **skills** are **not** part of the core binary install. Install them from each agent’s marketplace when available. See the install prompt for the marketplace gate.
+
+## Contributor / source install
+
+```bash
+git clone https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive
+cd hive
+bundle install
+./bin/hive --version
+# optional: ln -sf "$PWD/bin/hive" ~/.local/bin/hive
+```
+
+See [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md).
+
+## Building release tarballs
+
+```bash
+packaging/scripts/build_tarball.sh --platform linux-x86_64 --version v0.1.0 --out dist --sums
+```
+
+Tag `v*` pushes run [.github/workflows/release.yml](../.github/workflows/release.yml):
+
+1. `rake test`
+2. Package **linux-x86_64** + **darwin-arm64** tarballs (embedded Ruby + vendored gems; build fails if embed or `bundle install` fails)
+3. Clean-PATH smoke (`env -i PATH=/usr/bin:/bin`) so system Ruby cannot mask embed bugs
+4. Merge `SHA256SUMS`, rewrite Homebrew formula + AUR `PKGBUILD` with real checksums, optional tap push
+5. Publish GitHub Release assets (`install.sh`, tarballs, `SHA256SUMS`, formula, PKGBUILD)
+
+Packaging strategy (v1): **relocatable prefix** (app + `vendor/bundle` + launcher + embedded Ruby from the build host on release CI). Single-file Tebako packs were deferred because of bubbletea/lipgloss FFI risk.
+
+The bash installer **requires** a successful `SHA256SUMS` download and a local `sha256sum`/`shasum` tool; missing sums or a checksum mismatch is a hard fail.
