diff --git a/packaging/INSTALL_PROMPT.md b/packaging/INSTALL_PROMPT.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..0ccc8c56
--- /dev/null
+++ b/packaging/INSTALL_PROMPT.md
@@ -0,0 +1,68 @@
+# Install Hive (agent prompt)
+
+Paste this block into Claude Code, Codex, Pi, or another coding agent. It installs Hive via the best channel for the host OS, verifies the binary, runs soft dependency checks, and optionally runs `hive init`. **Skills are a separate package** — install them only through a real agent marketplace when supported.
+
+Version note: instructions match Hive release assets named `hive-vX.Y.Z-<platform>.tar.gz` (see GitHub Releases).
+
+```text
+Install Hive for me using the best native channel for this machine. Do not clone into ~/Dev/hive unless every packaged channel fails and the user confirms a source install.
+
+## Stop conditions (ask before changing anything)
+- If a working Hive is already on PATH (`hive --version` or `hv --version` prints a bare semver like 0.1.0), stop and ask whether to upgrade (`hive update`) or leave it.
+- If `command -v hive` points at Apache Hive or another unrelated binary, prefer installing as `hv` (bash channel) or ensure the package `hive` is earlier on PATH (brew/AUR).
+- Never overwrite an existing install directory, brew formula, or AUR package without asking.
+- Do NOT copy skill trees into ~/.claude, ~/.codex, or ~/.pi by hand. Skills install only via the agent marketplace when available.
+
+## Detect OS / arch
+- macOS arm64 → Homebrew tap (preferred)
+- Arch Linux x86_64 → AUR package hive-bin (preferred; yay or paru)
+- Ubuntu 22.04+ x86_64 / other Linux x86_64 → bash one-liner
+- Alpine, NixOS, BSDs, Windows (non-WSL) → stop and report unsupported for tier-1 packages; offer source install only if the user insists
+
+## Install
+
+### macOS (Homebrew)
+brew tap ivankuznetsov/hive
+brew install hive
+# or: brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive
+
+### Arch (AUR)
+yay -S hive-bin
+# or: paru -S hive-bin
+
+### Linux bash one-liner (also fallback)
+curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash
+# pin: HIVE_VERSION=v0.1.0 curl -fsSL ... | bash
+
+## Verify
+hive --version || hv --version
+command -v hive || command -v hv
+
+## Soft-check runtime CLIs (report missing; do not auto-install)
+git, bash, gh, jq, claude, and optionally codex / pi.
+Hints:
+- git / jq / bash → OS package manager
+- gh → https://cli.github.com/ then `gh auth login`
+- claude → Claude Code docs
+Run `hive doctor` (or `hv doctor`) and summarize missing rows.
+
+## Project bootstrap
+If the current directory is a git repository and the user wants Hive attached:
+  hive init .
+Non-interactive / CI: init skips the daemon service enable prompt.
+On a TTY, init may ask whether to register the hive daemon as a user service
+(systemd --user or launchd) and whether to enable+start it.
+
+## Skills (marketplace only)
+If this agent supports a marketplace/plugin install for Hive skills, offer to
+install the hive skills package after the binary works.
+Otherwise print: "Install hive skills from your agent marketplace when listed;
+they are not shipped inside the hive binary."
+Never invent a copy-paste tree under ~/.claude or equivalent.
+
+## Report back
+- channel used (brew / aur / bash)
+- version string and binary path
+- missing runtime CLIs
+- whether init ran and whether a service unit was registered
+```
