+---
+title: Hive::InstallChannel
+type: module
+source: lib/hive/install_channel.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [packaging, update, uninstall]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: Detects install channel (`brew` / `aur` / `bash` / `dev` / `unknown`) so `hive update` and `hive uninstall` never fight package managers.
+
+## Detection order
+
+1. `ENV["HIVE_INSTALL_CHANNEL"]`
+2. Marker file (`install-channel` under data root / `HIVE_PREFIX`)
+3. Heuristics:
+   - **brew**: Cellar/`opt/hive` ownership only — never a bare `brew --prefix` match (Intel Mac prefix is often `/usr/local`)
+   - **aur**: `pacman -Qo` ownership of `hive-bin`
+   - **bash**: marker or `~/.local/share/hive` prefix
+   - **dev**: git checkout + Gemfile
+4. `unknown`
+
+## Consumers
+
+- [[commands/update]] — shells out to brew / yay / install.sh
+- [[commands/uninstall]] — refuses to `rm` brew/AUR binaries
+
+## Related
+
+- [[modules/paths]] — install-channel marker path under data_root
+- [[modules/service_installer]] — user service units after `hive init`
