@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@
+---
+title: Hive::Paths
+type: module
+source: lib/hive/paths.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [paths, xdg, packaging, config]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: XDG-aware global path helpers. When `HIVE_HOME` is set, Hive uses a single-directory legacy layout. Otherwise config/data/state/cache split across XDG base dirs. Project pipeline state stays at `<project>/.hive-state/`.
+
+## Roots
+
+| Helper | Default (no `HIVE_HOME`) | With `HIVE_HOME` |
+|--------|--------------------------|------------------|
+| `config_root` | `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/hive` | `$HIVE_HOME` |
+| `data_root` | `${XDG_DATA_HOME:-~/.local/share}/hive` | `$HIVE_HOME` |
+| `state_root` | `${XDG_STATE_HOME:-~/.local/state}/hive` | `$HIVE_HOME` |
+| `cache_root` | `${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/hive` | `$HIVE_HOME/cache` |
+| `log_root` | `<state_root>/logs` | `$HIVE_HOME/logs` |
+| `bin_root` | `~/.local/bin` | `~/.local/bin` |
+
+Daemon/bot defaults: `daemon_pid_file`, `daemon_log_file`, `bot_pid_file`, `bot_log_file`, `bot_last_seen_file` under state/log roots.
+
+## Templates & services
+
+`templates_root` / `resolve_template` prefer packaged share (`HIVE_SHARE_ROOT`, `HIVE_PREFIX/share/hive`, or data_root templates), then the source-tree `templates/`. `services_root` resolves systemd/launchd unit templates for [[modules/service_installer]].
+
+## Related
+
+- [[modules/config]] — registry load/write + migration hook
+- [[modules/install_channel]] — `install-channel` marker under data_root
+- [[operating]] — operator paths for daemon/bot logs
